README for xorg-xf86-input-libinput


OVERLAY NOTES

The upstream build fails on this system's kernel headers: xf86libinput.c
references BTN_STYLUS3 (linux/input-event-codes.h), a button code added to
the kernel only around 2023 -- well after the kernel headers installed on
this board were generated. GCC reports it as undeclared.

This overlay adds compat-btn-stylus3.h, a small header defining just the
missing constant (value 0x149, its stable upstream numeric value, verified
against the kernel source), injected via `-include` in CFLAGS. This board's
kernel will never actually emit a BTN_STYLUS3 event either way (it predates
the code by even more), so the corresponding switch case in xf86libinput.c
is simply dead code here -- it only needed to compile, not run.
